Write a Java program that takes an integer as input and checks if it's positive, negative, or zero. Print an appropriate message based on the input.

import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int num = sc.nextInt();
        if(num==0){
            System.out.println("ZERO");
        }
        else if(num>0){
            System.out.println("POSITIVE");
        }
        else if(num<0){
            System.out.println("NEGATIVE");
        }
    }
}
